26namespace webrtc {
27
28class VCMReceiveCallback;
29
30enum { kDecoderFrameMemoryLength = 10 };
31
32class VCMDecodedFrameCallback : public DecodedImageCallback {
33 public:
34 VCMDecodedFrameCallback(VCMTiming* timing, Clock* clock);
35 ~VCMDecodedFrameCallback() override;
36 void SetUserReceiveCallback(VCMReceiveCallback* receiveCallback);
37 VCMReceiveCallback* UserReceiveCallback();
38
39 int32_t Decoded(VideoFrame& decodedImage) override;
40 int32_t Decoded(VideoFrame& decodedImage, int64_t decode_time_ms) override;
41 void Decoded(VideoFrame& decodedImage,
42 absl::optional<int32_t> decode_time_ms,
43 absl::optional<uint8_t> qp) override;
44
45 void OnDecoderImplementationName(const char* implementation_name);
46
47 void Map(uint32_t timestamp, const VCMFrameInformation& frameInfo);
48 void ClearTimestampMap();
49
50 private:
51 SequenceChecker construction_thread_;
52 // Protect |_timestampMap|.
53 Clock* const _clock;
54 // This callback must be set before the decoder thread starts running
55 // and must only be unset when external threads (e.g decoder thread)
56 // have been stopped. Due to that, the variable should regarded as const
57 // while there are more than one threads involved, it must be set
58 // from the same thread, and therfore a lock is not required to access it.
59 VCMReceiveCallback* _receiveCallback = nullptr;
60 VCMTiming* _timing;
61 Mutex lock_;
62 VCMTimestampMap _timestampMap RTC_GUARDED_BY(lock_);
63 int64_t ntp_offset_;
64 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-SlowDownDecoder to simulate a slow decoder.
65 FieldTrialOptional<TimeDelta> _extra_decode_time;
66
67 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-LowLatencyRenderer. The parameter |enabled|
68 // determines if the low-latency renderer algorithm should be used for the
69 // case min playout delay=0 and max playout delay>0.
70 FieldTrialParameter<bool> low_latency_renderer_enabled_;
71 // Set by the field trial WebRTC-LowLatencyRenderer. The parameter
72 // |include_predecode_buffer| determines if the predecode buffer should be
73 // taken into account when calculating maximum number of frames in composition
74 // queue.
75 FieldTrialParameter<bool> low_latency_renderer_include_predecode_buffer_;
76};
77
78class VCMGenericDecoder {
79 public:
80 explicit VCMGenericDecoder(std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> decoder);
81 explicit VCMGenericDecoder(VideoDecoder* decoder, bool isExternal = false);
82 ~VCMGenericDecoder();
83
84 /**
85 * Initialize the decoder with the information from the VideoCodec
86 */
87 int32_t InitDecode(const VideoCodec* settings, int32_t numberOfCores);
88
89 /**
90 * Decode to a raw I420 frame,
91 *
92 * inputVideoBuffer reference to encoded video frame
93 */
94 int32_t Decode(const VCMEncodedFrame& inputFrame, Timestamp now);
95
96 /**
97 * Set decode callback. Deregistering while decoding is illegal.
98 */
99 int32_t RegisterDecodeCompleteCallback(VCMDecodedFrameCallback* callback);
100
101 bool IsSameDecoder(VideoDecoder* decoder) const {
102 return decoder_.get() == decoder;
103 }
104
105 private:
106 VCMDecodedFrameCallback* _callback;
107 std::unique_ptr<VideoDecoder> decoder_;
108 VideoCodecType _codecType;
109 const bool _isExternal;
110 VideoContentType _last_keyframe_content_type;
111 VideoDecoder::DecoderInfo decoder_info_;
112};

114} // namespace webrtc
